@startuml
title Contact Management Application - Deployment and Control Flow

actor User
participant "Browser" as Browser
participant "NGINX\nLoad Balancer" as NGINX
participant "Angular Frontend\n(SSR)" as Frontend
participant "ASP.NET Core\nWeb API" as API
participant "MediatR\nCQRS Handler" as MediatR
participant "Application\nLayer" as Application
participant "Repository\nPattern" as Repository
participant "Entity Framework\nCore" as EF
participant "PostgreSQL\nDatabase" as DB
participant "Identity\nService" as Identity

== System Startup & Deployment ==
activate DB
note over DB: Container starts\nfrom PostgreSQL image
DB -> DB: Initialize database

activate API
note over API: Container starts\nfrom Api/Dockerfile
API -> DB: Run EF Core Migrations
activate DB
DB --> API: Migration completed
deactivate DB

API -> API: Initialize services\n(DI Container)
API -> Identity: Setup ASP.NET\nCore Identity
activate Identity
Identity --> API: Identity configured
deactivate Identity

activate Frontend
note over Frontend: Container starts\nfrom frontend/Dockerfile
Frontend -> Frontend: Build Angular app\nwith SSR

activate NGINX
note over NGINX: Container starts\nfrom loadbalancer/Dockerfile
NGINX -> NGINX: Load configuration\nAPI Gateway setup

== User Registration Flow ==
User -> Browser: Access registration page
Browser -> NGINX: GET /register
NGINX -> Frontend: Route request
activate Frontend
Frontend --> Browser: Registration form
deactivate Frontend

User -> Browser: Submit registration
Browser -> NGINX: POST /api/auth/register
NGINX -> API: Forward request
activate API
API -> MediatR: Send RegisterCommand
activate MediatR
MediatR -> Application: Handle command
activate Application
Application -> Identity: Create user account
activate Identity
Identity -> Repository: Persist user
activate Repository
Repository -> EF: Save entity
activate EF
EF -> DB: INSERT user
activate DB
DB --> EF: Success
deactivate DB
EF --> Repository: User created
deactivate EF
Repository --> Identity: Success
deactivate Repository
Identity --> Application: User registered
deactivate Identity
Application --> MediatR: Registration result
deactivate Application
MediatR --> API: Success response
deactivate MediatR
API --> NGINX: 201 Created + JWT
deactivate API
NGINX --> Browser: Registration success
Browser -> User: Show success message

== User Login Flow ==
User -> Browser: Access login page
Browser -> NGINX: GET /login
NGINX -> Frontend: Route request
activate Frontend
Frontend --> Browser: Login form
deactivate Frontend

User -> Browser: Submit credentials
Browser -> NGINX: POST /api/auth/login
NGINX -> API: Forward request
activate API
API -> MediatR: Send LoginCommand
activate MediatR
MediatR -> Application: Handle command
activate Application
Application -> Identity: Validate credentials
activate Identity
Identity -> Repository: Query user
activate Repository
Repository -> EF: Find user
activate EF
EF -> DB: SELECT user
activate DB
DB --> EF: User data
deactivate DB
EF --> Repository: User entity
deactivate EF
Repository --> Identity: User found
deactivate Repository
Identity -> Identity: Generate JWT token
Identity --> Application: Token + user info
deactivate Identity
Application --> MediatR: Login result
deactivate Application
MediatR --> API: Success with JWT
deactivate MediatR
API --> NGINX: 200 OK + JWT
deactivate API
NGINX --> Browser: Login success
Browser -> Browser: Store JWT token
Browser -> User: Redirect to dashboard

== Contact Management Flow ==
User -> Browser: View contacts
Browser -> NGINX: GET /contacts\n(Authorization: Bearer JWT)
NGINX -> Frontend: Route request
activate Frontend
Frontend -> NGINX: GET /api/contacts
NGINX -> API: Forward with JWT
activate API
API -> API: Validate JWT
API -> MediatR: Send GetContactsQuery
activate MediatR
MediatR -> Application: Handle query
activate Application
Application -> Repository: Get all contacts
activate Repository
Repository -> EF: Query contacts
activate EF
EF -> DB: SELECT * FROM contacts
activate DB
DB --> EF: Contact records
deactivate DB
EF --> Repository: Contact entities
deactivate EF
Repository --> Application: Contact list
deactivate Repository
Application --> MediatR: Contact DTOs
deactivate Application
MediatR --> API: Contact data
deactivate MediatR
API --> NGINX: 200 OK + JSON
deactivate API
NGINX --> Frontend: Contact data
Frontend --> Browser: Rendered contacts
deactivate Frontend
Browser -> User: Display contacts

== Create Contact Flow ==
User -> Browser: Create new contact
Browser -> NGINX: POST /api/contacts\n(Authorization: Bearer JWT)
NGINX -> API: Forward request
activate API
API -> API: Validate JWT\nCheck authorization
API -> MediatR: Send CreateContactCommand
activate MediatR
MediatR -> Application: Handle command
activate Application
Application -> Application: Validate business rules
Application -> Repository: Add contact
activate Repository
Repository -> EF: Add entity
activate EF
EF -> DB: INSERT contact
activate DB
DB --> EF: Contact created
deactivate DB
EF --> Repository: Success
deactivate EF
Repository --> Application: Contact entity
deactivate Repository
Application --> MediatR: Contact DTO
deactivate Application
MediatR --> API: Success response
deactivate MediatR
API --> NGINX: 201 Created
deactivate API
NGINX -> Frontend: Forward response
activate Frontend
Frontend --> Browser: Update UI
deactivate Frontend
Browser -> User: Show new contact

== Update Contact Flow ==
User -> Browser: Update contact
Browser -> NGINX: PUT /api/contacts/{id}\n(Authorization: Bearer JWT)
NGINX -> API: Forward request
activate API
API -> API: Validate JWT
API -> MediatR: Send UpdateContactCommand
activate MediatR
MediatR -> Application: Handle command
activate Application
Application -> Repository: Update contact
activate Repository
Repository -> EF: Update entity
activate EF
EF -> DB: UPDATE contact
activate DB
DB --> EF: Success
deactivate DB
EF --> Repository: Updated entity
deactivate EF
Repository --> Application: Success
deactivate Repository
Application --> MediatR: Updated DTO
deactivate Application
MediatR --> API: Success response
deactivate MediatR
API --> NGINX: 200 OK
deactivate API
NGINX -> Frontend: Forward response
activate Frontend
Frontend --> Browser: Update UI
deactivate Frontend
Browser -> User: Show updated contact

== Delete Contact Flow ==
User -> Browser: Delete contact
Browser -> NGINX: DELETE /api/contacts/{id}\n(Authorization: Bearer JWT)
NGINX -> API: Forward request
activate API
API -> API: Validate JWT\nCheck permissions
API -> MediatR: Send DeleteContactCommand
activate MediatR
MediatR -> Application: Handle command
activate Application
Application -> Repository: Delete contact
activate Repository
Repository -> EF: Remove entity
activate EF
EF -> DB: DELETE contact
activate DB
DB --> EF: Success
deactivate DB
EF --> Repository: Success
deactivate EF
Repository --> Application: Success
deactivate Repository
Application --> MediatR: Success result
deactivate Application
MediatR --> API: 204 No Content
deactivate MediatR
API --> NGINX: 204 No Content
deactivate API
NGINX -> Frontend: Forward response
activate Frontend
Frontend --> Browser: Update UI
deactivate Frontend
Browser -> User: Remove from display

@enduml
